Tag to be registered       : sgn-BE-nl

English name of language   : Belgian-Flemish Sign Language

Native name of language (transcribed into ASCII): vlaamse tekentaal

Reference to published description of the language (book or article):

DeDeyne, Grethe / Loncke, Filip: Een exploratieve studie naar enkele 
onderliggende principes in het gebruik van handconfiguraties in de 
vlaamse tekentaal. 1982 - 27 p. Manuscript

Loncke, Filip: The specific situation of the Flemish deaf people and 
their attitudes towards sign language. In: Kyle, Jim / Woll, Bencie 
(eds): Language in sign: An international perspective on sign 
language. (Proceedings of the Second International Symposium of Sign 
Language Research in Bristol, U.K. in July 1981). London : Croom Helm 
(1983) - pp. 159-162

Vermeerbergen, Myriam / DeVriendt, Sera: The repetition of signs in 
Flemish Sign Language. In: Ahlgren, Inger / Bergman, Brita / Brennan, 
Mary (eds): Perspectives on sign language structure: Papers from the 
Fifth International Symposium on Sign Language Research. Vol. 1; Held 
in Salamanca, Spain, 25-30 May 1992. Durham : isla (1994) - pp. 
201-214
